A man, believed to be in his 30s, was killed when he lost control of his car and it rolled on the R21 in Kempton Park in Ekurhuleni on Saturday, paramedics said. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene to find the wrecked car in the emergency lane of the road. The man s body was found in the drainage ditch, ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead. It was believed that the driver lost control of the car, causing it to roll and eject him, Meiring said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter